The paper deals with the problem of recovering complex-valued signals from linear measurements, which is a common problem in signal processing and information theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SP (Signal Processing) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also introduces a novel algorithm and derives state evolution equations, which are related to machine learning and optimization, respectively. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.MM (Multimedia), and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) are also possible sub-categories.
